  <description><![CDATA[<p>Surrounded by dramatic scenery, Lake Geneva is shared between France (40%) and Switzerland (60%). Our peaceful and elegant resort of Evian, famous for its mineral water, lies on the French southern shores at the foothills of the Chablais Alps where you can take hikes and bike rides.<br />Back at the lakeside you can take gentle strolls through the pretty towns along its shores, whilst ferries and sightseeing cruises operate all over this beautiful crescent-shaped lake. Destinations include the French town of Thonons-les-Bains, the medieval settlement of Yvoire which is listed as one of the most beautiful villages of France, and the famous Swiss centres of Geneva, Lausanne and Montreux.<br />A sunny spa town on the southern shores of Lake Geneva, Evian has a rich historical heritage and numerous gardens such as the Japanese Garden, English Garden and even the Lovers’ Garden - “oh là là!” You can even help yourself to Evian mineral water from the source behind the company’s art nouveau headquarters here</p>]]></description>
